{
  "texts": [
    "KGs can also reveal insights into the pathology of diseases since disease comorbidity reflects the shared molecular mechanisms or environmental factors between diseases (27).",
    "For example, KGs were used to make novel genedisease predictions for autism spectrum disorder (24).",
    "Within multimorbidity, KGs have the potential to accelerate a precision medicine approach to healthcare by efficiently combining knowledge from multiple datasets, including those relating genes, proteins, molecules, drug compounds, and diseases, to develop a better understanding of comorbidities or specific diseases.",
    "By further integrating patient clinical records into networks, graph representation learning of EHRs, and knowledge databases, we can generate predictions for disease and treatments tailored to individual patients that reduce the risk of ADRs (20, 73, 78).",
    "To customize medication recommendations for patients with complex health conditions and reduce drug-drug interactions, the Graph Augmented Memory Network (GAMENet) integrated a drug-drug knowledge graph with longitudinal patient EHR data."
  ]
}